President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster for the Havasupai Tribe and authorized federal aid to assist with recovery efforts after severe storms, flooding, and landslides occurred from July 11 to July 12, 2018. The federal funding will be used for emergency work, as well as repairs and replacements of damaged facilities. Hazard mitigation measures will also be supported. Nancy Casper has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made if requested by the Tribe and deemed necessary based on damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.